        "body": "### LeetCode Username\n\nkeshav_goel_21\n\n### Problem Number, Title, and Link\n\nhttps://leetcode.com/problems/power-of-three/description/\n\n### Bug Category\n\nMissing test case *(Incorrect/Inefficient Code getting accepted because of missing test cases)*\n\n### Bug Description\n\nclass Solution:\n    def isPowerOfThree(self, n: int) -> bool:\n        if n <= 0:\n            return False\n        largeNum = 3**20\n        return largeNum % n == 0\n\nIn the above code if n=(3**21) ,the ans should be true because n is a power of three. But due to missing test case with extreme large value of n, the above code got submitted despite it returns False when n=(3**21) ,which is wrong answer.\n\n### Language Used for Code\n\nPython/Python3\n\n### Code used for Submit/Run operation\n\n```bash\n\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThere should be a test case with extreme value of n (ex- 3**999888), so that no one can just create a large number like (3**20) and just returns weather the number  %n ==0 or not.\n\n### Screenshots\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
